page.title: 19KEELBY CHURCH
page.content: Keelby church is named St Barthomews.It is a Parish Church and every month it produces a magazine called Parish News.The magazine celebrates marriges,christenings and comformation and mourns death. The vicar is called Rev Hoggart.There is a choir with 19 members,adults and children.There is an organist and a choirmaster. As you come into the church on your left hand side you will see a stained glass window.It has not always been a stained window,unlike the main window,as we found out from the board at the back.The outside isle and pillars on the left are the oldest part of the church as they were there in Norman times.
